# Idle Hours — Co-op Jigsaw: Phase 1 Build Spec

## Project context

Idle Hours is a cozy games editorial site (Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, Sanity v5, GSAP, Framer Motion). The design system lives at idlehours.co.uk/staging — refer to it for all visual decisions. The site has five existing games at /play. We are building a sixth: a co-op multiplayer jigsaw puzzle.

The full feature will eventually include:
- Real image slicing via SVG clip paths applied to press kit JPGs
- Multiplayer via Supabase Realtime — piece positions, live cursors, player presence
- Named rooms with invite codes (4-letter word e.g. PINE)
- 200–2000 piece puzzles
- Snap detection based on adjacency to neighbouring pieces only, not absolute grid position
- Cluster movement — groups of connected pieces move together

## What we are building now: Phase 1

Phase 1 is the solo canvas. Fully playable single-player jigsaw with correct interaction feel. No networking, no Supabase, no rooms. The goal is to nail the canvas controls, piece interaction, and snap behaviour before any multiplayer layer is added.

## Game identity

This game needs a new entry added to lib/gameThemes.ts. The jigsaw is a slow, collaborative, communal game — it belongs to a warm brown/orange/cream world. Suggested name: Jigsaw.

